808; Lang, K., Lehtonen, M., Martikainen, P., Nitrification potentials at different pH values in peat samples from various layers of a drained mire (1993) Geomicrobiol. J., 11, pp. 141-147; Lovely, D.R., Klug, M.J., Sulfate reducers can outcompete methanogens at freshwater sulfate concentrations (1983) Appl. Environ. Microbiol., 45, pp. 187-192; McDonald, K.M., Cheng, L., Olson, M.P., Angle, R.P., A comparison of box and plume model calculations for sulphur deposition and flux in Alberta, Canada (1996) Atmos. Environ., 30, pp. 2969-2980; Meldan, B., Schnoor, J.L., Czechoslovakia: Examining a critically ill environment (1992) Environ. Sci. Technol., 26, pp. 14-21; Nedwell, D.B., The input and mineralisation of organic C in anaerobic equatic sediments (1984) Adv. Microbiol. Ecol., 7, pp. 93-131; Nedwell, D.B., Watson, A., CH4 production, oxidation and emission in a U.K. ombrotrophic peat bog: Influence of SO2-4 from acid rain (1995) Soil Biol. Biochem., 27, pp. 893-903; Novḱ, M., Bottrell, S.H., Fottová, D., Buzek, F., Groscheová, H., Žak, K., Sulfur isotope signals in forest soils of central Europe along an air pollution gradient (1996) Environ. Sci. Technol., 30, pp. 3473-3476; Novḱ, M., Bottrell, S.H., Přechová, Sulfur isotope inventories of atmospheric deposition, spruce forest floor and living Sphagnum along a NW-SE transect across Europe (2001) Biogeochemistry, 53, pp. 23-50; (1996) The SAS System for Windows, , SAS, version 6.12, SAS Inst., Cary, N. C; Schiff, S., Aravena, R., Mewhinney, E., Elgood, R., Warner, B., Dillon, P., Trumbore, S., Precambrian shield wetlands: Hydrologic control of the sources and export of dissolved organic matter (1998) Clim. Change, 40, pp. 167-188; Spratt, H.G., Morgan, M.D., Good, R.E., Sulfate reduction in peat from a New Jersey pinelands cedar swamp (1987) Appl. Environ. Microbiol., 53, pp. 1406-1411; Stumm, W., Morgan, J.J., (1981) Aquatic Chemistry: an Introduction Emphasizing Chemical Equilibria in Natural Waters, , John Wile